 <title>Make Your Front-End Workflow Scalable and Efficient</title>
 <link>https://dev-2014drupalcampcoloradoorg.pantheonsite.io/session/make-your-front-end-workflow-scalable-and-efficient</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-session-room field-type-entityreference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Room:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;Aten Room (Class 101)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the complexity and scale of your projects grow, so can your headaches related to merge conflicts, software version incompatibilities and browser testing. We’ll take a look at the how and why of maintaining a scalable front-end workflow with tools like RVM, Bundler, Sass and Compass.&lt;/p&gt;
